<doc id="995061" wikidata="Q6839689" url="?curid=995061" title="Micromonosporaceae">
<text>Micromonosporaceae is a family of bacteria of the class &quot;Actinomycetia&quot;. They are gram-positive, spore-forming soil organisms that form a true mycelium.

==Phylogeny==
The currently accepted taxonomy is based on the List of Prokaryotic names with Standing in Nomenclature (LPSN) and National Center for Biotechnology Information (NCBI).


Genera incertae sedis:



* &quot;Solwaraspora&quot;&quot; 

